## Plan (settled before code; recommendations confirmed by user)

### Q1 — TeacherAssignment shape (spec-locked, phase-1.md:180-204)
`teacher × classArm × subject × academicYear × (optional term)`. Direct
FKs to classArm + subject — NOT through ClassSubject (ClassSubject is
classLevel×subject; a teacher teaches a specific arm, not a level).
Unique `(schoolId, teacherId, classArmId, subjectId, academicYearId,
termId)`, `termId` nullable (null = whole year, set = term-specific).
Closest to candidate (c), plus year scoping + optional per-term override.

### Q2 — cardinality
Teacher→many assignments: yes. **Co-teaching ALLOWED** (no app guard):
`teacherId` is inside the unique key, so two teachers can share an
(arm, subject, year, term). Matches the schema; supports lab/team
teaching. Tightening later is a cheap app-rule; loosening is a migration.
- NOTE: the DB unique treats NULL term as DISTINCT (Postgres), so two
  identical whole-year (termId=NULL) rows would NOT collide at the DB.
  The service adds a pre-check (match incl. null term) returning a clean
  409 TEACHER_ALREADY_ASSIGNED, with the P2002 catch as a backstop for the
  non-null race. The "duplicate" spec case asserts this.

### Q3 — scope filter (lands cp2; reconciliation noted here for when it does)
Lives in the SERVICE layer (needs DB access to teacher_assignments; it's
in-school authorization, not tenancy; PermissionsGuard isn't wired until
slice 13). **Spec drift to reconcile in cp2:** phase-1.md:1150's example
`user.roles.includes('teacher')` cannot work as written — AuthContext is
role-free by design (auth-context.ts; roles are re-fetched, see
role-check.ts). cp2's `getTeacherScope` re-fetches roleKeys the same way
`assertUserActiveAndHasOneOf` does. **Record this drift in the cp2 journal
entry when cp2 lands.**

### Q3a — teacher endpoint surface (confirmed: dedicated)
Teachers hit ONLY a small set of dedicated `/teacher-*` scope-filtered
read endpoints (cp2). All admin CRUD stays owner|admin and rejects
teachers outright — smallest security surface (phase-1.md:1265 risk note).

### Q4 — teacher portal minimum (cp3)
- /teacher/dashboard — "Welcome. You are assigned to: <arms + subjects>."
- /teacher/classes — arms in scope (subject-assignment ∪ homeroom).
- /teacher/classes/[armId] — roster + this teacher's subjects; 404 if
  armId ∉ scope (the testable security property).
- /teacher/profile — already shipped slice 10; untouched.
No timetable/grading/announcements (Phase 2/4).

