## cp2 progress (teacher scope filter — landed, awaiting review; nothing committed)

### Q3 spec-drift reconciliation (RESOLVED in code)
phase-1.md:1150 shows the scope check as
`if (user.roles.includes('teacher')) { ... }`. **That cannot work in this
codebase** — `AuthContext` (apps/api/.../auth/auth-context.ts) is role-free
by design: it carries only `sessionId`, `userId`, `schoolId`, with a header
comment "Roles and permissions are NOT included — handlers that need them
re-fetch via withTenant" (the no-stale-permissions rationale). So cp2 does
NOT read roles off the JWT/AuthContext. Instead it re-fetches the user +
role grants under withTenant via the established
`assertUserActiveAndHasOneOf(authCtx, ["teacher"])` (apps/api/.../auth/
role-check.ts) — the exact pattern every admin endpoint already uses, just
gated on `teacher` instead of `owner|admin`. This is the one spec-vs-code
divergence flagged in the cp1 plan; it is now reconciled and tested
(getMyScope as admin → 403 proves roles come from the DB, not the token).

### Built
- packages/types/src/teacher-scope/ — TeacherScopeDto, ENRICHED (post-review
  extension): `classArms: [{id,name,code}]` +
  `subjectsByArm: Record<armId, [{id,name,code}]>` (TeacherScopeArmDto /
  TeacherScopeSubjectDto), plus a TRIMMED TeacherRosterStudentDto +
  TeacherRosterResponse. Registered in the types barrel.
- apps/api modules/teacher-scope/teacher-scope.helper.ts — `getTeacherScope(
  db, teacherId, year?)`: subject-assignment arms (active only, optional
  year filter) ∪ homeroom arms (ClassArm.classTeacherId, active). Two
  queries, unioned in code — no N+1. Each arm/subject carries {id,name,code}
  pulled via a select-widening on the SAME two queries (no extra round-
  trips). Pure over (db, teacherId, year?); caller owns the withTenant
  boundary. subjectsByArm stays a Map in the helper; the service converts to
  the wire Record (the Map-in-helper / Record-on-wire split cp2 already used).
- teacher-scope.service.ts — getMyScope + getMyArmRoster, both gated
  `["teacher"]` via the role re-fetch above. Roster returns current-term
  students of ONE in-scope arm; out-of-scope/cross-tenant arm → 404 (not
  403) so the arm reads as non-existent, matching RLS semantics.
- teacher-scope.controller.ts — GET /teacher-scope/me and
  GET /teacher-scope/me/arms/:armId/students. Thin pass-through; no admin
  branch (Q3a — dedicated teacher surface).
- module registered in app.module.

